# OPENAKTA — tooling context

## Before you edit

- Living architecture: `docs/active_architecture/` and index in `DOCS-INDEX.md`.
- What the backend **actually** guarantees today: `business-core/` (code wins over stale docs).
- Tasking and roadmaps live outside this repo (issue tracker); do not confuse docs with runtime contracts.

## Rust (repo root)

Aliases in `.cargo/config.toml` (aligned with `.github/workflows/rust-ci.yml`):

- `cargo fmt-check` — same as CI.
- `cargo lint` — clippy workspace, `-D warnings`.
- `cargo test-all` — default suite (excludes `#[ignore]`).
- `cargo test-slow` — ignored / heavy tests only.

MSRV and policy: `CONTRIBUTING.md` and `docs/RUST_TOOLING_BASELINE.md`.

## Desktop (Electron + Next)

- App code: `apps/desktop/` (Prettier and ESLint are scoped to this app).
- Do not relax rules outside `components/ai-elements/**` without aligning with code owners.

## TypeScript SDKs / integrations

- Packages under `sdks/**` and `integrations/**`: scripts in each `package.json`; `pnpm` from the root with filters (see root `package.json`).

## Protocol buffers

- Generation: `proto:gen` script at the repo root (`package.json`) — do not hand-edit generated output.

## Avoid

- Do not move folders or rename crates in this iteration (separate decision).
- Do not assume production billing/tenancy/auth just because old Markdown mentions it — see `business-core/`.
